vq - Video Queue

USAGE:
    vq [-force] [-extract-audio] [-profiles=profile1,profile2] [-v URL]

DESCRIPTION:
    Queue a video for download. By default, gets the video URL
    from the clipboard. Automatically starts downloading in the
    background if another instance isn't running.

OPTIONS:
    -force
        Force queue even if video was previously queued

    -extract-audio
        Extract audio only

    -profiles=profile1,profile2
        Use specified profiles (space-separated)

    -v URL
        Specify URL to download instead of clipboard

    -*
        Pass options directly to youtube-dl

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-videos-audio-format FORMAT
        Audio format for extraction (default: aac)

    -conf-videos-youtube-download-cmd CMD
        YouTube download command (default: yt-dlp)

    -conf-videos-youtube-video-download-options OPTIONS
        Download options for video files

EXAMPLES:
    vq
    vq -v https://youtube.com/watch?v=123
    vq -extract-audio
    vq -force -profiles=high-quality,low-quality
